## Issue 3: Consent Flow ‚Äî Redesign as Chat Conversation

**Current:** Single screen with allocation bar and consent input.

**Change:** 4-step progressive chat flow in left panel, allocation visual in right panel.

**Implementation:**

Create a multi-step consent flow:

```jsx
const CONSENT_STEPS = [
  {
    id: 'recommendation',
    message: `Based on your answers, here's your recommended allocation:

‚óè Foundation (65%) ‚Äî Stable assets
‚óè Growth (30%) ‚Äî Balanced growth
‚óè Upside (5%) ‚Äî Higher potential

This balances protection with growth.`,
    button: 'Continue'
  },
  {
    id: 'risk',
    message: `With this allocation:

üìà Good year: +15-25%
üìâ Bad quarter: -10-15%
‚è±Ô∏è Recovery: typically 3-6 months

Markets are uncertain. This is not a guarantee.`,
    button: 'I understand'
  },
  {
    id: 'control',
    message: `You're always in control:

‚úì Adjust allocation anytime
‚úì Protect assets against drops
‚úì Borrow without selling
‚úì Exit to cash whenever`,
    button: 'Continue'
  },
  {
    id: 'consent',
    message: `Ready to start? Type this to confirm:`,
    consentRequired: true
  }
];

const ConsentFlow = ({ allocation, onComplete }) => {
  const [currentStep, setCurrentStep] = useState(0);
  const [messages, setMessages] = useState([]);
  const [consentInput, setConsentInput] = useState('');
  
  const consentSentence = 'ŸÖÿ™Ÿàÿ¨Ÿá ÿ±€åÿ≥⁄© ÿß€åŸÜ ÿ≥ÿ®ÿØ ÿØÿßÿ±ÿß€å€å ÿ¥ÿØŸÖ Ÿà ÿ®ÿßŸáÿßÿ¥ ŸÖŸàÿßŸÅŸÇ Ÿáÿ≥ÿ™ŸÖ.';
  
  const handleContinue = () => {
    const step = CONSENT_STEPS[currentStep];
    setMessages(prev => [...prev, { type: 'bot', content: step.message }]);
    
    if (currentStep < CONSENT_STEPS.length - 1) {
      setCurrentStep(currentStep + 1);
    }
  };
  
  const handleConfirm = () => {
    if (consentInput.trim() === consentSentence) {
      onComplete();
    }
  };
  
  return (
    <div className="consent-flow">
      <div className="chat-messages">
        {messages.map((msg, i) => (
          <div key={i} className="chat-message bot">
            <div className="message-content">{msg.content}</div>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
      
      <div className="chat-input-area">
        {CONSENT_STEPS[currentStep].consentRequired ? (
          <>
            <div className="consent-sentence">{consentSentence}</div>
            <div className="consent-translation">
              I understand the risk of this portfolio and I agree with it.
            </div>
            <input
              type="text"
              className="consent-input"
              dir="rtl"
              value={consentInput}
              onChange={(e) => setConsentInput(e.target.value)}
              placeholder="Type the sentence above..."
            />
            <button 
              className="btn-primary"
              onClick={handleConfirm}
              disabled={consentInput.trim() !== consentSentence}
            >
              Confirm
            </button>
          </>
        ) : (
          <button className="btn-primary" onClick={handleContinue}>
            {CONSENT_STEPS[currentStep].button}
          </button>
        )}
      </div>
    </div>
  );
};
```

```css
.consent-flow {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  height: 100%;
}

.chat-messages {
  flex: 1;
  overflow-y: auto;
  padding: 16px;
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  gap: 16px;
}

.chat-message.bot {
  background: var(--bg-secondary);
  border-radius: 12px;
