## Issue 9: History ‚Äî Status Badges to Expandable Detail

**Current:** Status transition badges (`BALANCED ‚Üí ATTENTION REQUIRED`) shown inline.

**Change:** Move to expandable detail view.

**Implementation:**

```jsx
const HistoryEntry = ({ entry }) => {
  const [expanded, setExpanded] = useState(false);
  const formatted = formatHistoryEntry(entry);
  const hasDetails = entry.statusChange || entry.details;
  
  return (
    <div className="history-entry">
      <div className="history-entry-main">
        <span className={`history-icon ${formatted.iconClass}`}>
          {formatted.icon}
        </span>
        <span className="history-text">{formatted.text}</span>
        {formatted.amount && (
          <span className="history-amount">
            {formatIRR(formatted.amount)}
          </span>
        )}
        <span className="history-time">{formatTime(entry.timestamp)}</span>
        {hasDetails && (
          <button 
            className="history-expand-btn"
            onClick={() => setExpanded(!expanded)}
          >
            {expanded ? '‚àí' : '+'}
          </button>
        )}
      </div>
      
      {expanded && hasDetails && (
        <div className="history-entry-details">
          {entry.statusChange && (
            <div className="status-change">
              <span className={`status-badge ${entry.statusChange.from.toLowerCase()}`}>
                {entry.statusChange.from}
              </span>
              <span className="status-arrow">‚Üí</span>
              <span className={`status-badge ${entry.statusChange.to.toLowerCase()}`}>
                {entry.statusChange.to}
              </span>
            </div>
          )}
          {entry.details && (
            <div className="entry-details-text">{entry.details}</div>
          )}
        </div>
      )}
    </div>
  );
};
```

