## Issue 12: History ‚Äî Group by Date

**Current:** All entries show full timestamp "Jan 12, 10:XX PM".

**Change:** Group entries by day with section headers.

**Implementation:**

```jsx
const groupByDate = (entries) => {
  const groups = {};
  const today = new Date().toDateString();
  const yesterday = new Date(Date.now() - 86400000).toDateString();
  
  entries.forEach(entry => {
    const date = new Date(entry.timestamp).toDateString();
    let label;
    
    if (date === today) {
      label = 'Today';
    } else if (date === yesterday) {
      label = 'Yesterday';
    } else {
      label = new Date(entry.timestamp).toLocaleDateString('en-US', {
        month: 'short',
        day: 'numeric'
      });
    }
    
    if (!groups[label]) groups[label] = [];
    groups[label].push(entry);
  });
  
  return groups;
};

const HistoryList = ({ entries }) => {
  const grouped = groupByDate(entries);
  
  return (
    <div className="history-list">
      {Object.entries(grouped).map(([date, items]) => (
        <div key={date} className="history-group">
          <div className="history-date-header">{date}</div>
          {items.map((entry, i) => (
            <HistoryEntry key={i} entry={entry} />
          ))}
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>
  );
};
```

```css
.history-group {
  margin-bottom: 24px;
}

.history-date-header {
  font-size: 12px;
  font-weight: 600;
  color: var(--text-muted);
  text-transform: uppercase;
  letter-spacing: 0.5px;
  padding: 8px 0;
  border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
  margin-bottom: 8px;
}
```

When grouped by date, show only time (not full date) in each entry:

```jsx
// In HistoryEntry, format time only (since date is in header)
<span className="history-time">{formatTimeOnly(entry.timestamp)}</span>

const formatTimeOnly = (timestamp) => {
  return new Date(timestamp).toLocaleTimeString('en-US', {
    hour: 'numeric',
    minute: '2-digit',
    hour12: true
  });
};
```

